# CAN / ECU data → UI

## UDP path (typical daemon → gauges)
- **`udpreceiver`:** binds **UDP port 45454**; each datagram treated as text **`"<id>,<value>"`** (comma-separated).
- **`processPendingDatagrams()`:** `switch(ident)` → **`m_dashboard->set…(Value)`** (rpm, speed, etc.).
- **`Connect::openConnection`:** for CAN ECU mode starts **`m_udpreceiver->startreceiver()`**; daemons are selected elsewhere (`daemonstartup`, `startdaemon.sh`).

## SocketCAN path (`Extender`)
- **`Extender::openCAN`:** creates **`socketcan`** device **`can0`**; **`framesReceived` → `readyToRead()`** reads **`QCanBusFrame`**, updates **`m_dashboard`** (including **`setcan(QStringList)`** for raw id + hex payload).

## QML consumption
- **`Connect`** registers **`Dashboard`** on the QML engine; gauges use **`Dashboard.<property>`** or dynamic **`Dashboard[sourcename]`** (e.g. `createsquaregaugeUserDash.js`).
